Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Casa Grande, Maple, Relapasa, Telefonica

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-13T19:18:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/peru-stocks-atacocha-casa-grande-maple-relapasa-telefonica.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:59 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index rose 1.8 percent to 21,862.91. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 0.9 percent to 2,778.91.  Industrial stocks and utilities rose as investors bet a
weekend election poll will show Congresswoman Keiko Fujimori
widening her lead over former army rebel Ollanta Humala before
the June 5 runoff vote, said SAB Inteligo analyst Daniel Mori.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer
and a unit of Gloria SA, gained 4 percent to 15.50 soles after
futures advanced in New York.  Telefonica del Peru SAA (TELEFBC1)  (TELEFBC1
PE), the local unit of Telefonica SA, rose 2.5 percent to 2.90
soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 2.3 percent to 90 cents.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol
YPF SA known as Relapasa, rose 2.1 percent to 1.91 soles.  Grana
y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1 PE), the Peruvian construction company,
climbed 2.4 percent to 6.40 soles.  Miners gained after copper, zinc and silver advanced in New
York and  London .  Gold Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAC1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields
Ltd., jumped 11 percent to 5.85 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru, rose 3.1
percent to $1.34 after announcing first-quarter net income rose
fivefold to $1.3 million. Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE),
the Lima-based silver and zinc producer, gained 2.5 percent to
1.21 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
